# public/ — Web Root

## Purpose
PHP entry point + static asset destination. Nginx's document root is /var/www/html/public.

## Contents
- index.php          PHP bootstrap — requires autoload, instantiates Application, runs router
- assets/            React build assets (JS/CSS bundles) — built into here by Docker
- *.html             React SPA pages (index.html etc) — copied from client/dist/ by Docker
- (other static)     Any other static files served directly by Nginx

## Important
- The React build output from client/ is copied INTO this directory at Docker build time
- Nginx serves /assets/* with 1-year immutable cache headers
- DO NOT manually edit files here that come from the React build — edit in client/src/ instead
- PHP handles all routes not matched by Nginx SPA rewrites or /api/node/* proxy
